Missing values ('n/a') denote cases where the respective program could not determine a result.
Read classification was determined against a database containing only SARS-CoV-2 and human with Kraken2 (v2.1.1).
Nucleotide identity, mismatches, Ns and QC pass status were determined with PRESIDENT (v0.6.3).
QC pass criteria are the RKI genome submission requirements: >= 90% identity to NC_045512.2, <= 5% Ns, etc. (PDF in german).
Lineage and the corresponding tree resolution conflict measure were determined with Pangolin (v3.1.17 using PangoLEARN data release 2021-12-06).
Constellation and the corresponding tree resolution conflict measure were determined with Scorpio (v0.3.16 using Constellations version 0.1.1).
Clade, mutations, deletions and insertions were determined with Nextclade (v1.8.1 using nextclade data release 2022-01-05).
Note: amino acid insertions are currently not reported directly by Nextclade, and were instead converted from nucleotide insertions with custom code when possible (adapted from Codon2Nucleotide).
